      "span_text": "We likewise observed increased binding of α-catenin to APC. α-Catenin is reported to indirectly associate with APC via β-catenin,  these three proteins contact each other at microtubule ends.  Cytosolic complexes of α-and β-catenin have also been described. 63 Thus dynamic α-catenin binding to APC is most likely due to its association with increased levels of β-catenin."
